    "didYouKnow": [
      "The mole is the only SI base unit that uses a specific number (Avogadro's constant) as its definition."
    ],
    "summary": [
      "Chemistry starts with understanding matter and measuring it accurately using significant figures.",
      "Pure substances have fixed properties; mixtures do not."
    ],
    "quickRevision": [
      "Remember: Leading zeros don't count. Trailing zeros after a decimal DO count."
    ]
